you wrote:
"This being  my first long trip in my 1975 newly restored  Westy. I =
would really appreciate it  if
 any of you experienced folks would give me advice as to where I could =
camp cheaply while on the road, (newly retired couple) and what to look
for as far as security"

My wife and I have been known to camp at those truck stops - Circle J =
maybe, I'm not sure of the names.  Anyway, you don't have to go off of =
the highway and there is usually a shower there that you can use in the =
morning for a modest fee.  My wife was very reluctant to do this at =
first but in a pinch they work great - at least in Canada.  We prefer =
camp grounds of course but when you are in a pinch - those things work =
great.  I think I would be quite reluctant to stay in those kinds of =
places in the U.S. though.

jdd 60 std

